@startuml
title StreamingToolExecutor - Per-Tool State Machine

skinparam backgroundColor #F7F1E6
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam TitleFontSize 19
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam NoteFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F2E9D9
  BorderColor #1D1D1D
  FontColor #161616
  ArrowColor #5E5A53
  StartColor #8C2721
  EndColor #161616
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}

[*] --> Queued

state "Queued" as Queued
state "Gated\ncanExecuteTool? +\npermission check" as Gated #F5EBDD
state "Executing" as Executing #EFE6D8
state "Progress\nstreamed update" as Progress
state "Completed" as Completed #EFE6D8
state "Yielded\nin safe order" as Yielded #E8DDD0
state "Synthetic Error\ndenied / aborted /\nsibling failed" as Synth #F5EBDD

Queued --> Gated : eligibility check
Gated --> Executing : approved
Gated --> Synth : denied / not ready
Executing --> Progress : partial output
Progress --> Executing : resume
Executing --> Completed : done
Executing --> Synth : interrupt / abort
Completed --> Yielded : release in order
Synth --> Yielded : injected as tool_result

Yielded --> [*]

note right of Yielded
  Yield order matches the
  assistant's tool_use block
  order, even when execution
  finished out of order.
end note

note right of Synth
  Failures are not thrown
  upward; they become
  tool_results so the loop
  can keep moving.
end note

@enduml
